You work as the IT staff in a company, a new intern Sam started today.You received an email from HR to create Sam in the system with all the necessary credentials.
Create user Sam
Give Sam password Sam#123
Create group interns
Add Sam to the interns group
Grant group interns read only priviledges to the /tmp folder your created in Day4
NB: Kindly outline the steps you took to finish this task.

Solution
I navigated to my Desktop directory using the cd /Desktop/linuxx command.

I confirmed that the tmp directory created in Day4 already existed inside the linuxx folder using ls command.

I created a new user named Sam using the sudo useradd -m Sam command.

I set Sam’s password to Sam#123 using the sudo passwd Sam command.

I created a group named interns using the sudo groupadd interns command.

I added Sam to the interns group using the sudo usermod -aG interns Sam command.

I changed the group ownership of the tmp directory using the sudo chgrp interns tmp command.

I granted read and execute (read-only) privileges to the interns group using the sudo chmod 750 tmp command.

I verified the changes using the ls -ld tmp command.

